Title : Ingrid Rivera Rocafort
Text : {{Like resume|date=September 2015}}

{{spanish name|Rivera|Rocafort}}
'''Ingrid I. Rivera Rocafort''' is a marketing professional and the current Executive Director of the [[Puerto Rico Tourism Company]]. She has worked as a [[Marketing strategy|market analyst]], strategic planner, and Director of such firms as [[Procter & Gamble]], [[Walmart|Wal-Mart]], and Advent-Morro Equity Partners coordinating efforts in [[Puerto Rico]] and for [[Spanish language|Spanish]]-speaking markets throughout the [[Caribbean]] and [[United States]]. She also is a public speaker on topics related to travel and business.<ref>{{Cite journal|url = http://search.ebscohost.com/login.aspx?direct=true&db=bth&AN=101107573&site=ehost-live|title = Puerto Rico Seeks to Revive Direct UK Flights|last = Noakes|first = Gary|date = 5 February 2015|journal = Travel Trade Gazette UK & Ireland|doi = |pmid = |access-date = 21 September 2015|issue = 3133|page = 8|url-access=subscription }}</ref>

==Biography==
Rivera has a bachelor's degree in Business Administration from the<ref name="CoC bio">{{cite web|title=Ingrid I. Rivera Rocafort Directora Ejecutiva Designada de la Compañía de Turismo de Puerto Rico|url=http://www.camarapr.org/Pres-Izq/Foro-Eco/Bio-Ingrid-Rivera.pdf|website=Camara Puerto Rico|publisher=Puerto Rico Chamber of Commerce|accessdate=21 September 2015|location=San Juan, Puerto Rico|language=Spanish|date=2013}}</ref> [[University of Puerto Rico, Río Piedras Campus]]<ref name="Carib Journal">{{cite news|title=Ingrid Rivera Rocafort Appointed to Lead Puerto Rico Tourism Company|url=http://caribjournal.com/2012/11/30/ingrid-rivera-rocafort-appointed-to-lead-puerto-rico-tourism-company/#|accessdate=21 September 2015|publisher=Carib Journal|date=30 November 2012|location=Miami, Florida}}</ref> with a specialty in Marketing. In 1980, she began working for [[Procter & Gamble]] and worked her way up to Director of External Relations in the Multicultural Division,<ref name="CoC bio" /> where she was responsible for product positioning throughout the Caribbean, Puerto Rico, and for the US [[Hispanic]] market.<ref name="New Day">{{cite news|title=La nominada a Turismo se propone "pulir" la marca Puerto Rico y su oferta|url=http://www.elnuevodia.com/negocios/finanzas/nota/ingridrivera-1408268/|accessdate=21 September 2015|publisher=El Nuevo Dia|date=16 December 2012|location=Puerto Rico|language=Spanish}}</ref> After  26&nbsp;years she took retirement in 2006 and founded and acted as President of Rive Consulting Corporation, simultaneously serving on the External Advisory Board for [[Wal-Mart]] US until 2008. Rivera joined Advent-Morro Equity Partners as Director<ref name="CoC bio" /> in 2010. She headed investor relations,<ref name="New Day" /> of the venture capital, private equity firm<ref name=Advent-Morro>{{cite web|title=Company Overview of Advent-Morro Equity Partners|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/private/snapshot.asp?privcapId=18611|website=Bloomberg Business|publisher=Bloomberg Business|accessdate=21 September 2015}}</ref> which involved strategic planning and analysis for venture capitalists<ref name="New Day" /> interested in Puerto Rican start-ups or those in the US Latino market.<ref name="CoC bio" />

In 2012 Rivera was tapped by Puerto Rican Governor [[Alejandro García Padilla]]<ref name="CoC bio" /> to serve as the Executive Director of the [[Puerto Rico Tourism Company]] (PRTC). In her confirmation hearings, she was supported for her experience and business acumen from the former director of the Tourism Company, Terestella González; the President of the Convention Center, Milton Segarra; and the director of the Industrialists Association of Puerto Rico<ref name=hearings>{{cite news|last1=Cordero|first1=Gerardo|title=Ingrid Rivera revela su plan estratégico para impulsar el turismo|url=http://www.primerahora.com/noticias/gobierno-politica/nota/ingridriverarevelasuplanestrategicoparaimpulsarelturismo-925301/|accessdate=21 September 2015|publisher=Primera Hora|date=30 May 2013|location=San Juan, Puerto Rico|language=Spanish}}</ref> and was unanimously confirmed by the [[Puerto Rican Senate|Senate]].<ref name="confirmation">{{cite news|last1=Banuchi|first1=Rebecca|url=http://www.primerahora.com/noticias/policia-tribunales/nota/senadoconfirmaaingridriverarocafortcomodirectoradeturismo-926285/|title=Senado confirma a Ingrid Rivera Rocafort como directora de Turismo|accessdate=2014-04-30|publisher=Primera Hora|date=3 June 2013|location=San Juan, Puerto Rico|language=Spanish}}</ref>

In her capacity as the Executive Director of the PRTC, she is able to make decisions regarding the tourism marketplace without being swayed by partisan politics in the country.<ref>{{Cite journal|url = http://search.ebscohost.com/login.aspx?direct=true&db=bth&AN=89039021&site=ehost-live|title = Tourism Sector Responds to PRTC Director's Remarks|last = Costa|first = Dennis|date = 11 July 2013|journal = Caribbean Business|doi = |pmid = |access-date = 21 September 2015|volume = 41|issue = 26|page = 6|url-access=subscription }}</ref> In addition, PRTC provides business owners with education about new regulations and laws regarding tourism and casinos.<ref>{{Cite journal|url = http://search.ebscohost.com/login.aspx?direct=true&db=bth&AN=99121350&site=ehost-live|title = New Regulations a Game-Changer for Casino Sector|last = Costa|first = Dennis|date = 23 October 2014|journal = Caribbean Business|doi = |pmid = |access-date = 21 September 2015|volume = 42|issue = 41|pages = 5–6|url-access=subscription }}</ref>

After confirmation, Rivera had developed a plan for growing Puerto Rico's tourism sector from 6% to 8% of the [[gross domestic product]] (GDP) for the island by 2016, utilizing market analysis and evaluation of air traffic routes, among other factors.<ref name="Caribbean Business">{{cite journal|title=Ingrid Rivera charts a course to grow Puerto Rico tourism|journal=Caribbean Business|date=27 June 2013|volume=41|issue=24|url=http://www.cb.pr/prnt_ed/ingrid-rivera-charts-a-course-to-grow-puerto-rico-tourism-8689.html|accessdate=21 September 2015|publisher=Casiano Communications|location=San Juan, Puerto Rico}}</ref> Despite economic problems in Puerto Rico, the tourism industry has remained stable under Riveras direction through 2015, though growth has not increased in all sectors. Some sectors, like the [[cruise ship]] sector have seen increases of over 25% while others, like the convention sector and [[casino]] segment are struggling. Rivera has worked with the cruise industry to increase the number of ships stopping at the [[port of San Juan]].<ref>{{Cite journal|url = http://search.ebscohost.com/login.aspx?direct=true&db=bth&AN=87331751&site=ehost-live|title = P.R. Tourism Co. Says Carnival Will Continue to Visit San Juan|last = Costa|first = Dennis|date = 18 April 2013|journal = Caribbean Business|doi = |pmid = |access-date = 21 September 2015|volume = 41|issue = 14|pages = 4–6|url-access=subscription }}</ref> Rivera has developed marketing strategies like partnerships with the [[Golf Channel]] to pinpoint beneficial relationships rather than widespread coverage in traditional television marketing and through legislation to address infrastructure and incentive shortfalls.<ref name="2015 analysis">{{cite journal|last1=Schoene Roura|first1=Philipe|last2=Costa|first2=Dennis|title=Puerto Rico’s tourism weathering the economic storm|journal=Caribbean Business|date=13 August 2015|volume=43|issue=31|url=http://www.caribbeanbusinesspr.com/prnt_ed/puerto-ricos-tourism-weathering-the-economic-storm-11522.html|accessdate=21 September 2015|publisher=Casiano Communications I|location=San Juan, Puerto Rico}}</ref> In March, 2015, Rivera's work was recognized by the First Lady of Puerto Rico, [[Wilma Pastrana]] as one of the outstanding women in public service in Puerto Rico.<ref name="Tribuna">{{cite news|title=Primera dama reconoce a mujeres destacadas en el servicio público|url=http://tribunapr.com/2015/03/24/primera-dama-reconoce-a-mujeres-destacadas-en-el-servicio-publico.html|accessdate=21 September 2015|publisher=Tribuna|date=24 March 2015|location=San Juan, Puerto Rico|language=Spanish}}</ref>

In addition to her business work, Rivera is also involved in non-profit service, being an active member of the [[New America Alliance]], Since 1995, he has been part of the Board of Directors of the [[YMCA]] in San Juan and the [[P&G Alumni Network]] serving as a board member.<ref name="CoC bio" /><!--this last sentence really is not needed-->

